            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Warranty Compliance Requirements: Most manufacturer warranties require specific conditions for coverage validity: proper attic ventilation meeting minimum 1:150 ratio (inadequate ventilation voids many warranties), annual professional inspections documenting roof condition, prompt repair of any damage (neglected damage can void coverage), no unauthorized modifications or repairs by unqualified contractors, and retention of installation documentation and warranty certificates. We provide all required documentation and guidance for maintaining warranty compliance.\n\nCommon Warranty Exclusions: Understanding exclusions prevents claim disappointments. Typical exclusions include damage from acts of nature (wind, hail) unless specific coverage purchased, normal wear and tear, installation over inadequate ventilation, damage from foot traffic or roof maintenance, algae/fungus growth (unless algae-resistant shingles specified), and improper building construction affecting roof performance. Some exclusions can be addressed through upgraded products (algae-resistant shingles, impact-resistant shingles) or proper installation practices (adequate ventilation, proper fastening). Review warranty terms carefully and ask questions before installation ensuring you understand coverage limits and requirements."
